      },
      "edited" : false,
      "score" : 59,
      "creation_date" : 1392827142,
      "post_id" : 16066990,
      "comment_id" : 33140514,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "<code>.toString()</code> will work but the proper function is <code>.name()</code>. 99.9% toString is not the answer."
    }, {
      "owner" : {
        "account_id" : 46157,
        "reputation" : 11111,
        "user_id" : 136276,
        "user_type" : "registered",
        "accept_rate" : 62,
        "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/Ms0Bi.jpg?s=256",
        "display_name" : "Roger",
        "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/136276/roger"
      },
      "edited" : false,
      "score" : 1,
      "creation_date" : 1392827715,
      "post_id" : 16066990,
      "comment_id" : 33140961,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "btw <code>.displayName()</code> will also work unless it is overridden for localization as intended."
    }, {
      "owner" : {
        "account_id" : 1063749,
        "reputation" : 14277,
        "user_id" : 1064809,
        "user_type" : "registered",
        "accept_rate" : 70,
        "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/b1cf3eaad6d6c7bd5995351132923cac?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
        "display_name" : "Natix",
        "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1064809/natix"
      },
      "edited" : false,
      "score" : 40,
      "creation_date" : 1416393225,
      "post_id" : 16066990,
      "comment_id" : 42554923,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "You don&#39;t really need to call <code>name()</code> at all. You can directly pass the <code>Charset</code> object into the <code>InputStreamReader</code> constructor."
    }, {
      "owner" : {
        "account_id" : 2815255,
        "reputation" : 5872,
        "user_id" : 2420519,
        "user_type" : "registered",
        "accept_rate" : 50,
        "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/0d30c42d5ee2da9d89a8c146000a7dc6?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
        "display_name" : "Hai Zhang",
        "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/2420519/hai-zhang"
      },
      "edited" : false,
      "score" : 1,
      "creation_date" : 1423202970,
      "post_id" : 16066990,
      "comment_id" : 45061945,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "Note that in Andorid, this require API level 19+."
    }, {
      "owner" : {
        "account_id" : 1522669,
        "reputation" : 12028,
        "user_id" : 1421925,
        "user_type" : "registered",
        "accept_rate" : 90,
        "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/cLzpB.jpg?s=256",
        "display_name" : "Magnilex",
        "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1421925/magnilex"
      },
      "edited" : false,
      "score" : 7,
      "creation_date" : 1425306770,
      "post_id" : 16066990,
      "comment_id" : 45896448,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "And there are other libs out there which do require a <code>String</code>, perhaps because of legacy reasons. In such cases, I keep a <code>Charset</code> object around, typically derived from <code>StandardCharsets</code>, and use <code>name()</code> if needed."
    }, {
      "owner" : {
        "account_id" : 494704,
        "reputation" : 5447,
        "user_id" : 1225882,
        "user_type" : "registered",
        "accept_rate" : 100,
        "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/vSHZ9.jpg?s=256",
        "display_name" : "anothernode",
        "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1225882/anothernode"
      },
      "edited" : false,
      "score" : 1,
      "creation_date" : 1499956804,
      "post_id" : 16066990,
      "comment_id" : 77140240,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "The result for <code>name()</code>, <code>toString()</code> and just putting <code>StandardCharsets.UTF-8</code> directly is all the same because <code>Charset.toString()</code> just calls <code>Charset.name()</code> and if you use <code>StandardCharsets.UTF-8</code> in a place where a String is expected <code>Charset.toString()</code> will be called automatically."
    }, {
      "owner" : {
        "account_id" : 2580314,
        "reputation" : 3622,
        "user_id" : 2237148,
        "user_type" : "registered",
        "accept_rate" : 0,
        "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/id7kK.jpg?s=256",
        "display_name" : "Moti Bartov",
        "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/2237148/moti-bartov"
      },
      "edited" : false,
      "score" : 0,
      "creation_date" : 1702826073,
      "post_id" : 16066990,
      "comment_id" : 136938497,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "When I used only toString(), on Android6 it returned &quot;java.nio.charset.CharsetICU[UTF-8]&quot;, definitely not what I wanted. Using .name() returned the correct value &quot;UTF-8&quot;"
    } ],
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 46157,
      "reputation" : 11111,
      "user_id" : 136276,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 62,
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/Ms0Bi.jpg?s=256",
