      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/136276/roger"
    },
    "is_accepted" : true,
    "score" : 1003,
    "last_activity_date" : 1748217652,
    "last_edit_date" : 1748217652,
    "creation_date" : 1366221704,
    "answer_id" : 16066990,
    "question_id" : 6698354,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>In Java 1.7+, the class <a href=\"https://docs.oracle.com/javase/7/docs/api/java/nio/charset/StandardCharsets.html\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">java.nio.charset.StandardCharsets</a> defines constants for <code>Charset</code> including <a href=\"https://docs.oracle.com/javase/7/docs/api/java/nio/charset/StandardCharsets.html#UTF_8\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><code>UTF_8</code></a>.</p>\n<pre><code>import java.nio.charset.StandardCharsets;\n\n...\n\nStandardCharsets.UTF_8.name();\n</code></pre>\n<p><strong>For Android: minSdk 19</strong></p>\n"
  }, {
    "comments" : [ {
      "owner" : {
        "account_id" : 5006676,
        "reputation" : 6447,
        "user_id" : 4024146,
        "user_type" : "registered",
        "profile_image" : "https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/-6kHBYaTT2sw/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAPZ0/AZk9LqXdwR4/s256-rj/photo.jpg",
        "display_name" : "mtrakal",
        "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/4024146/mtrakal"
      },
      "edited" : false,
      "score" : 2,
      "creation_date" : 1551890391,
      "post_id" : 32987975,
      "comment_id" : 96808721,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "it&#39;s removed from OkHttp, so next way is: <code>Charset.forName(&quot;UTF-8&quot;).name()</code> when you need support for lower Android than API 19+ otherwise you can use: <code>StandardCharsets.UTF_8.name()</code>"
    } ],
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 146433,
      "reputation" : 52702,
      "user_id" : 356895,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 66,
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/022ac4ee5fc9f2474d60c9a1a6dd16f5?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "JJD",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/356895/jjd"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 5,
    "last_activity_date" : 1444208300,
    "creation_date" : 1444208300,
    "answer_id" : 32987975,
    "question_id" : 6698354,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>If you are using <a href=\"http://square.github.io/okhttp/\" rel=\"noreferrer\">OkHttp</a> for Java/Android you can use the following constant:</p>\n\n<pre class=\"lang-java prettyprint-override\"><code>import com.squareup.okhttp.internal.Util;\n\nUtil.UTF_8; // Charset\nUtil.UTF_8.name(); // String\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 4059905,
      "reputation" : 1295,
      "user_id" : 3541666,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 0,
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/CqnPy.jpg?s=256",
      "display_name" : "Vazgen Torosyan",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/3541666/vazgen-torosyan"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 5,
    "last_activity_date" : 1522060472,
    "creation_date" : 1522060472,
    "answer_id" : 49489382,
    "question_id" : 6698354,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Constant definitions for the standard. These\n  charsets are guaranteed to be available on every implementation of the Java\n  platform.  since 1.7   </p>\n\n<pre><code> package java.nio.charset;\n Charset utf8 = StandardCharsets.UTF_8;\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 6739787,
      "reputation" : 1448,
      "user_id" : 5193370,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/Toyc6.jpg?s=256",
      "display_name" : "Mostafa Vatanpour",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/5193370/mostafa-vatanpour"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 10,
    "last_activity_date" : 1532360815,
    "creation_date" : 1532360815,
    "answer_id" : 51482715,
    "question_id" : 6698354,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>In Java 1.7+</p>\n\n<p>Do not use \"UTF-8\" string, instead use <code>Charset</code> type parameter:</p>\n\n<pre><code>import java.nio.charset.StandardCharsets\n\n...\n\nnew InputStreamReader(new FileInputStream(file), StandardCharsets.UTF_8);\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 3171905,
      "reputation" : 11474,
      "user_id" : 2680640,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/2zdCg.jpg?s=256",
      "display_name" : "sendon1982",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/2680640/sendon1982"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 4,
    "last_activity_date" : 1589168700,
    "creation_date" : 1589168700,
    "answer_id" : 61721965,
    "question_id" : 6698354,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>Class <code>org.apache.commons.lang3.CharEncoding.UTF_8</code> is deprecated after Java 7 introduced <code>java.nio.charset.StandardCharsets</code></p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>@see <a href=\"http://docs.oracle.com/javase/6/docs/technotes/guides/intl/encoding.doc.html\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">JRE character encoding names</a></li>\n<li>@since 2.1</li>\n<li>@deprecated Java 7 introduced {@link java.nio.charset.StandardCharsets}, which defines these constants as</li>\n<li>{@link Charset} objects. Use {@link Charset#name()} to get the string values provided in this class.</li>\n<li>This class will be removed in a future release.</li>\n</ul>\n"
  } ],
